olive oil
1 cucumber
1 tin sweetcorn
1 packet beef mince
1 packet tomato paste
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend
½ cup water
1 tsp brown sugar
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Plant-Based Mayo

• Thinly slice cucumber into sticks. Drain the sweetcorn.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat.
• Cook beef mince and sweetcorn, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• SPICY! The spice blend is mild, but use less if you're sensitive to heat. Add tomato paste and Tex-Mex spice blend and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add the water and brown sugar and simmer until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes.

TIP: For best results, drain any excess oil from the pan after cooking beef mince!

• Meanwhile, combine shredded cabbage mix and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil in a medium bowl.
• Microwave mini flourtortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts, until warmed through.

• Top tortillas with slaw, Mexican beef mince and cucumber.
• Drizzle over plant-based mayo to serve. Enjoy!